[2026-07-21] [Ask My Docs / Chat Interface] — Finding (Chunk 10.0 probe, build time): streamlit.testing.v1.AppTest re-executes the whole target script fresh on every .run() call. patch("app.streamlit_app.answer_with_verified_citations", ...) -- patching the re-bound name inside the script itself -- does NOT work, since the re-exec silently overwrites it. patch.object on the SOURCE module (citations.pipeline.answer_with_verified_citations) does work, confirmed with both st.button and st.chat_input. All Chunk 10.4+ tests patch source modules, not streamlit_app.py's own names.
